products.title: Rick's Clubstyle Triple Tree for OEM Speedo (Road Glide 2014-2023)

products.title: Baja LP6 Driving/Combo (Night Rod Special 2014+)
products.body_html:
LP6 Pro Driving/Combo comes with bracket and wiring harness for 2014-2017 Harley-Davidson Night Rod Special.

The LP6 Pro is a 6-inch powerhouse featuring a total of 11,225 total lumens and of 200-degree spread of usable LED light thanks to the dedicated peripheral lighting of our patented Integrated Peripheral Technology (IPT). To keep your light performing at its highest potential, the LP6 integrates our proprietary Direct Ducted Cooling (DDC) technology. This feature allows air to travel through the front of the housing, over the rear heat sinks – drastically improving cooling capacity and performance. With an colored daytime running light, low power, and high-power mode, the LP6 easily fulfills all your lighting needs.

The LP6 Pro is available in multiple patterns to suit your needs. The Driving/Combo pattern provide maximum trail coverage in a single light. The Driving/Combo pattern is equipped with both Driving (42 degrees) and spot (8 degrees) optics to provide you with a smooth blend of light for both near-field applications and distance (Lighting Zones, 1,2, 3). The Spot pattern is a longer and narrower 8-degree beam focus for illumination further down the trail or road (Lighting Zone 4 & 5) and is designed to be used in conjunction with additional wide cornering and/or driving/combo auxiliary lights.

The addition of red, blue, or green backlight options alongside our original amber on the LP6 Pro gives enthusiasts the choice to customize their vehicle for shows, photo shoots or anywhere they want to bring attention.

It provides a clean, sleek, and lower-profile look on the tank and serves as a replacement for the original cover when relocating fittings to the headlight mask using our offset. Made from high-quality ABS plastic—not GRP—this precisely fitting part is milled on advanced 5-axis CNC machines. Installation on 2018–2020 models requires shortening the original dash cover holders and drilling new holes; a new bracket is included. Newer models feature an additional retaining bracket for secure mounting. Available in two finishes: paint-ready for easy customization or glossy black for a polished look without painting.

products.title: Cult-Werk Headlight Mask CUSTOM (Scout Bobber 2018+)
products.body_html: The Cult-Werk "Custom" headlight mask is designed to give all Indian Scout Bobber models from 2018 onward a slimmer, more aggressive front profile. It retains the original Indian headlight, which can also be swapped for an LED version with the same mounting. Made from premium ABS plastic—not GRP—the kit includes a CNC-lasered mask holder that ensures a precise and secure fit. The speedometer stays in its original position, and no cable modifications are needed. All mounting holes are pre-drilled, and the mask attaches firmly to the original mounting points. The headlight remains adjustable for optimal beam alignment, with the mask moving accordingly. Available in two finishes: paint-ready for easy customization or glossy black for a polished look without painting.

products.title: Cult-Werk Swinging Rear Fender (Softail Narrow 2018+)

products.title: Cult-Werk Fork Cover Kit "Long Version" (Scout Bobber 2018+)
products.body_html: The Cult-Werk 6-piece "Long Version" fork cover kit in black is designed for Indian Scout Bobber models from 2018 onward. It includes aluminum lower covers or folding linings and covers the fork tubes above, between, and below the clamps, provided the original mask and turn signals with holders are removed. This kit gives the fork a more robust, fully blacked-out appearance and is compatible with both original and custom front fenders. Each cover attaches securely with hidden threaded pins that self-center on the fork tubes, while bevels matching the fork bridges ensure perfectly aligned gaps. Crafted from high-quality aluminum, milled on advanced 5-axis CNC machines, and finished with glossy black powder coating, these covers guarantee top-tier quality. Installation is straightforward—simply slide the upper and lower covers over the fork tubes and fasten. The lower cover features a discreet cutout for fender access. Available in two versions: pure aluminum or with folding linings.

products.title: Cult-Werk Rear fender LOW (Sportster 2004+)
products.body_html: The Cult-Werk rear fender for Sportster models from 2004 onward is precision-milled on advanced 5-axis CNC machines to ensure a perfect fit as a direct replacement for the original fender. Finished to the highest standards, it requires checking the spring travel after installation due to its depth; if necessary, use a spring travel limiter (item HD-UNI033) or consider stiffening the dampers. Note that the original frame may need shortening, and original struts are no longer compatible—short fender struts (item HD-SPO006) are recommended. This fender is compatible only with very short solo seats (not possible on Sportster models from 2016) or select Cult-Werk seats (items HD-SPO068, HD-SPO069, and HD-SPO113). Available in two finishes: paint-ready with a flawless surface or glossy black that shines without painting, saving you time and cost.
